Israeli Stocks: Brainsway, Israel Chemicals, Nextcom

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-27T14:10:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/israeli-stocks-brainsway-and-nextcom-advance-fundtech-retreats.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index gained for the
first time in three days, rising 0.6 percent to 1,209.23 at the
4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded shares and
convertible securities valued at about 1.29 billion shekels
($375 million).  The following stocks rose or fell. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Brainsway Ltd. (BRIN)   climbed to the highest level since
June 5, gaining 5.1 percent to 27.96 shekels. The maker of
devices to treat neurological disorder received approval from
the institutional review board to begin trials on patients
suffering from obesity.  Israel Chemical Ltd. (ICL IT) fell to the lowest in a week,
retreating 1.4 percent to 50.80 shekels. Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu and Finance Minister Yuval Steinitz said  Dead Sea 
Works, a unit of the company that harvests minerals from the
Dead Sea to make fertilizer, will have to provide funding to
preserve the tourist area around the sea.  Nextcom Ltd. (NXTM)   increased 2.1 percent to 1.49
shekels, the highest close in three months. The provider of
communications systems won a 70 million-shekel tender from
Israel’s Defense Ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
{Sharon Wrobel} in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
